Class RegionalZone

  • java.lang.Object
    • simpplle.comcode.RegionalZone
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ColoradoFrontRange, ColoradoPlateau, EastsideRegionOne, Gila, GreatPlainsSteppe, MixedGrassPrairie, NorthernCentralRockies, SierraNevada, SouthCentralAlaska, SouthernCalifornia, SouthwestUtah, Teton, WesternGreatPlainsSteppe, WestsideRegionOne

    public abstract class RegionalZone
extends java.lang.Object
    The University of Montana owns copyright of the designated documentation contained within this file as part of the software product designated by Uniform Resource Identifier UM-OpenSIMPPLLE-1.0. By copying this file the user accepts the University of Montana Open Source License Contract pertaining to this documentation and agrees to abide by all restrictions, requirements, and assertions contained therein.     This is an abstract class containing fields and methods common to all zones. This class is not instantiated but rather serves as a common type for zones for use throughout this software.

      • getImageDir

        public java.lang.String getImageDir()
        Makes and gets the Image directory for this regional zone. An example of this from the sierra nevada regional zone: ("knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada" , "images"). This will make a pathname of "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/images"
        Returns:
        the image directory. from above example: "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/images"

      • getGisDir

        public java.lang.String getGisDir()
        Gets the GIS Directory for this Regional zone. Must call to the utility class to make the pathname. Example: From the Regional zone sierra nevada. ("knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada" , "gis"). This will make a pathname of "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/gis"
        Returns:
        pathname with zoneDir/gisDir from above example: "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/gis"

      • getWildlifeDir

        public java.lang.String getWildlifeDir()
        Gets the wildlife directory by passing to Utility class to make the pathname with zonedir and datadir, then passing that again to utility to make pathname. "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/data" , "wildlife". This will make a pathname of "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/data/wildlife"
        Returns:
        wildlife directory. from above example: "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/data/wildlife"

      • getSampleAreasDir

        public java.lang.String getSampleAreasDir()
        Gets a File which is the directory where the zones sample areas are stored. "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada" , "sample-areas". This will make a pathname of "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/sample-areas"
        Returns:
        the directory contains a zones sample area files. from above example: "knowledge/zones/sierra-nevada/sample-areas"

      • addFmz

        public void addFmz(Fmz fmz)
        Adds a fire management zone to the hash table that contains all the fire management zones for this regional zone.
        Parameters:

      • removeFmz

        public void removeFmz(Fmz fmz)
        Removes a fire management zone from this regional zone by removing it from the zone's fmz hashtable. Also updates the current area's fire management zones, which in turn updates all the EVU's who position is in this fmz, which are then reset to default fmz.
        Parameters:
        fmz - the fire management zone to be removed.

      • removeAllFmz

        public void removeAllFmz()
        Removes all fire management zones for this regional zone by clearing the allFmz hashtable. Also updates the current area's fire management zones, which in turn updates all the EVU's who position is in this fmz, which are then reset to default fmz.
